my purse along with debit card checkbook and dl was stolen what personal info can some get from them i didn't have any credit cards in the purse just the atm card and i immediately closed my bank account and debit card i'm just worried about the person trying to open new lines of credit under my name as a law enforcement officer i've seen this happen many times you've started taking the right steps already by closing your bank account with your driver's license and many other things the average person keeps in their wallet purse it is amazingly easy to open new lines of credit or a plethora of other things one key question is was your ssn card in your purse if it was this will help a criminal steal your identity even quicker granted without your ssn it is possible to find it using the information he has but having it to begin with will only give them a head start you most certainly want to file a report with your local law enforcement agency additionally you can contact the credit bureaus and alert them to the fact you are a potential victim of identity theft your bank undoubtedly has measures in place to help their customers who face this situation and can easily put you on the right track best of luck to you Identity theft Surveillance Phishing Bank fraud Debit card Plame affair Identity document Smart card Internet fraud Password Credit card fraud Automatic teller machine Credit card Bank Electronic money Credit repair Child support Privacy EFTPOS Pickpocketing British national identity card Beltway sniper attacks SmartRider Hong Kong Police Force Online Copyright Infringement Liability Limitation Act Probation officer Driver's license CPU cache Two-factor authentication Loyalty program Ulster Bank Money Bond Electronic toll collection Poker jargon Prostitution Cross site scripting Cheque National identification number Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus ChoicePoint Grand Theft Auto (game) Trademark Monopoly (game) Citigroup Cheating in Counte